cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with synthesizing the 3D Ken Burns effect from a single image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and rendering, which falls under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of neural networks for depth prediction and refinement suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves video synthesis, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
